  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Asia Foundation PPA with DFID CHASE is helping to address common challenges to peaceful state-society relations in fragile states, subnational conflict and post-conflict areas and transitional states at risk of renewed conflict. This activity represents analytical activities, including field research, surveys, and engagement with academics and practitioners. The purpose of these activities are to draw on the Foundation&apos;s field experience and knowledge to inform and influence aid practice and policy. This activity represents a range of regional programs, including Pakistan, Thailand, Sri Lanka, India, and the Philippines during the period Oct-Dec 2015.</narrative>
  </description>
